obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (1156)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Procedure for inquiry under section 19.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1156&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Procedure for inquiry under section 19.--(1) On receipt of a reference from the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or a statutory authority or on its own knowledge or information`
  line `received under section 19, if the Commission is of the opinion that there exists a prima facie case, it shall`
  line `direct the Director General to cause an investigation to be made into the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the subject matter of an information received is, in the opinion of the Commission,`
  line `substantially the same as or has been covered by any previous information received, then the new`
  line `information may be clubbed with the previous information.`
  line
  line `(2) Where on receipt of a reference from the Central Government or a State Government or a`
  line `statutory authority or information received under section 19, the Commission is of the opinion that there`
  line `exists no prima facie case, it shall close the matter forthwith and pass such orders as it deems fit and send`
  line `a copy of its order to the Central Government or the State Government or the statutory authority or the`
  line `parties concerned, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) The Commission may not inquire into agreement referred to in section 3 or conduct of an`
  line `enterprise or group under section 4, if the same or substantially the same facts and issues raised in the`
  line `information received under section 19 or reference from the Central Government or a State Government`
  line `or a statutory authority has already been decided by the Commission in its previous order.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Director General shall, on receipt of direction under sub-section (1), submit a report on his`
  line `findings within such period as may be specified by the Commission.`
  line
  line `^2[(3A) If, after consideration of the report of the Director General referred to in sub-section (3), the`
  line `Commission is of the opinion that further investigation is required, it may direct the Director General to`
  line `investigate further into the matter.`
  line
  line `(3B) The Director General shall, on receipt of direction under sub-section (3A), investigate the matter`
  line `and submit a supplementary report on his findings within such period as may be specified by the`
  line Commission.]
  line
  line `(4) The Commission may forward a copy of the report referred to in ^3[sub-section (3) and (3B)] to the`
  line `parties concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the investigation is caused to be made based on reference received from the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government or the statutory authority, the Commission shall forward a`
  line `copy of the report referred to in ^3[sub-section (3) and (3B)] to the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government or the statutory authority, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) If the report of the Director General referred to in ^3[sub-section (3) and (3B)] recommends that`
  line `there is no contravention of the provisions of this Act, the Commission shall invite objections or`
  line `suggestions from the Central Government or the State Government or the statutory authority or the parties`
  line `concerned, as the case may be, on such report of the Director General.`
  line
  line `(6) If, after consideration of the objections or suggestions referred to in sub-section (5), if any, the`
  line `Commission agrees with the recommendation of the Director General, it shall close the matter forthwith`
  line `and pass such orders as it deems fit and communicate its order to the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government or the statutory authority or the parties concerned, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) If, after consideration of the objections or suggestions referred to in sub-section (5), if any, the`
  line `Commission is of the opinion that further investigation is called for, it may direct further investigation in`
  line `the matter by the Director General or cause further inquiry to be made in the matter or itself proceed with`
  line `further inquiry in the matter in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(8) If the report of the Director General referred to in ^3[sub-section (3) and (3B)] recommends that`
  line `there is contravention of any of the provisions of this Act, and the Commission is of the opinion that`
  line `further inquiry is called for, it shall inquire into such contravention in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act.]`
  line
  line `^4[(9) Upon completion of the investigation or inquiry under sub-section (7) or sub-section (8), as the case may be, the Commission may pass an order closing the matter or pass an order under section 27, and send a copy of its order to the Central Government or the State Government or the statutory authority or the parties concerned, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that before passing such order, the Commission shall issue a show-cause notice indicating the contraventions alleged to have been committed and such other details as may be specified by regulations and give a reasonable opportunity of being heard to the parties concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 19, for section 26 (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 19 (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "sub-section (3)" (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  line
  line `4. ns. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-9-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (1157)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Orders by Commission after inquiry into agreements or abuse of dominant position.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1157&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Where after inquiry the Commission finds that any agreement referred to in section 3 or action of an`
  line `enterprise in a dominant position, is in contravention of section 3 or section 4, as the case may be, it may`
  line `pass all or any of the following orders, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) direct any enterprise or association of enterprises or person or association of persons, as the`
  line `case may be, involved in such agreement, or abuse of dominant position, to discontinue and not to`
  line `re-enter such agreement or discontinue such abuse of dominant position, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) impose such penalty, as it may deem fit which shall be not more than ten per cent. of the average of the turnover or income, as the case may be, for the last three preceding financial years, upon each of such person or enterprise which is a party to such agreement or has abused its dominant position:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case any agreement referred to in section 3 has been entered into by a cartel, the Commission may impose upon each producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider included in that cartel, a penalty of up to three times of its profit for each year of the continuance of such agreement or ten per cent. of its turnover or income, as the case may be, for each year of the continuance of such agreement, whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this clause, the expression "turnover" or "income", as the`
  line `case may be, shall be determined in such manner as may be specified by regulations..`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of this clause, "turnover" means global turnover derived from all the products and services by a person or an enterprise.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) direct that the agreements shall stand modified to the extent and in the manner as may be specified in the order by the Commission;`
  line
  line `(e) direct the enterprises concerned to abide by such other orders as the Commission may pass and comply with the directions, including payment of costs, if any;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(g) pass such other ^5[order or issue such directions] as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that while passing orders under this section, if the Commission comes to a finding,`
  line `that an enterprise in contravention to section 3 or section 4 of the Act is a member of a group as`
  line `defined in clause (b) of the Explanation to section 5 of the Act, and other members of such a group`
  line `are also responsible for, or have contributed to, such a contravention, then it may pass orders, under`
  line `this section, against such members of the group.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 20, for the proviso (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 6-3-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Cl. (c) omitted by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Cl. (f) omitted by Act 39 of 2007, s. 20 (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "order" (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `6. The Proviso inserted by s.20, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (1158)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Division of enterprise enjoying dominant position.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1158&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[Commission] may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, by order in writing,`
  line `direct division of an enterprise enjoying dominant position to ensure that such enterprise does not abuse`
  line `its dominant position.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, the order referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer or vesting of property, rights, liabilities or obligations;`
  line
  line `(b) the adjustment of contracts either by discharge or reduction of any liability or obligation or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(c) the creation, allotment, surrender or cancellation of any shares, stocks or securities;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(e) the formation or winding up of an enterprise or the amendment of the memorandum of`
  line `association or articles of association or any other instruments regulating the business of any`
  line enterprise;
  line
  line `(f) the extent to which, and the circumstances in which, provisions of the order affecting an`
  line `enterprise may be altered by the enterprise and the registration thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which may be necessary to give effect to the division of the enterprise.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any contract`
  line `or in any memorandum or articles of association, an officer of a company who ceases to hold office as`
  line `such in consequence of the division of an enterprise shall not be entitled to claim any compensation for`
  line `such cesser`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "Central Government, on recommendation under clause (f) of section 27" (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Cl. (d) omitted by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-20090`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (1159)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Procedure for investigation of combinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1159&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Commission is of the ^1[prima facie] opinion that a combination is likely to cause, or has caused an appreciable adverse effect on`
  line `competition within the relevant market in India, it shall issue a notice to show cause to the parties to combination calling upon them to respond ^2[within fifteen days] of the receipt of the notice, as to why investigation in respect of such combination should not be conducted.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) After receipt of the response of the parties to the combination under sub-section (1), the Commission may call for a report from the Director General and such report shall be submitted by the Director General within such time as the Commission may direct.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1B) The Commission shall, within thirty days of receipt of notice under sub-section (2) of section 6, form its prima facie opinion referred to in sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission, if it is prima facie of the opinion that the combination has, or is likely to have,an appreciable adverse effect on competition, it shall, ^4[within seven days] from the date of receipt of the response of the parties to the combination, ^1[or the receipt of the report from Director General called under sub section (1A), whichever is later] direct the parties to the said combination to publish details of the combination ^5[within seven days] of such direction, in such manner, as it thinks appropriate, for bringing the combination to the knowledge or information of the public and persons affected or likely to be affected by such combination.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may invite any person or member of the public, affected or likely to be affected by the said combination, to file his written objections, if any, before the Commission ^6[within ten days] from the date on which the details of the combination were published under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission may, ^7[within seven days] from the expiry of the period specified in sub-section (3), call for such additional or other information as it may deem fit from the parties to the said combination.`
  line
  line `(5) The additional or other information called for by the Commission shall be furnished by the parties`
  line `referred to in sub-section (4) ^8[within ten days] from the expiry of the period specified in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `^9[(6) After receipt of all information, the Commission shall proceed to deal with the case in accordance with the provisions contained in section 29A or section 31, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the Commission may accept appropriate modifications offered by the parties to the combination or suo motu propose modifications, as the case may be, before forming a prima facie opinion under sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007 s. 22, (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 21, for "within thirty days" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
