  line `4. 6. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "within seven working days" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "within ten working days" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 21, ibid, for "within fifteen working days" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "within fifteen working days" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "within fifteen days" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (92906)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 32
  title `Issue of statement of objections by Commission and proposal of modifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 22, (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=92906&sectionno=29A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[29A. Issue of statement of objections by Commission and proposal of modifications.--(1) Upon completion of the process under section 29, where the Commission is of the opinion that the combination has, or is likely to have, an appreciable adverse effect on competition, it shall issue a statement of objections to the parties identifying such appreciable adverse effect on competition and direct the parties to explain within twenty-five days of receipt of the statement of objections, why such combination should be allowed to take effect.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the parties to the combination consider that such appreciable adverse effect on competition`
  line `can be eliminated by suitable modification to such combination, they may submit an offer of appropriate`
  line `modification to the combination along with their explanation to the statement of objections issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Commission does not accept the modification submitted by the parties under sub-section (2)`
  line `it shall, within seven days from the date of receipt of the proposed modifications under that sub-section,`
  line `communicate to the parties as to why the modification is not sufficient to eliminate the appreciable`
  line `adverse effect on competition and call upon the parties to furnish, within twelve days of the receipt of the`
  line `said communication, revised modification, if any, to eliminate the appreciable adverse effects on`
  line `competition:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission shall evaluate such proposal for modification within twelve days from`
  line `receipt of such proposal:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Commission may suo motu propose appropriate modifications to the combination which may be considered by the parties to the combination.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (1160)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 33
  title `Inquiry into disclosures under sub-section (2) of section 6.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 23, for section 30 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1160&sectionno=30&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Procedure in case of notice under sub-section (2) of section 6.--Where any person or`
  line `enterprise has given a notice under sub-section (2) of section 6, the Commission shall examine such`
  line `notice and form its prima facie opinion as provided in sub-section (1) of section 29 and proceed as per`
  line `provisions contained in that section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (1161)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 34
  title `Orders of Commission on certain combinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1161&sectionno=31&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `31. Orders of Commission on ^1*** combinations.--(1) Where the Commission is of the opinion that any combination does not, or is not likely to, have an appreciable adverse effect on competition, it shall, by order, approve that combination ^2*** in respect of which a notice has been given under subsection (2) of section 6.`
  line
  line `^3[ Provided that if the Commission does not form a prima facie opinion as provided under sub-section (1B) of section 29, the combination shall be deemed to have been approved and no separate order shall be required to be passed.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Commission is of the opinion that the combination has, or is likely to have, an appreciable adverse effect on competition, it shall direct that the combination shall not take effect.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Where the Commission is of the opinion that any appreciable adverse effect on competition that the combination has, or is likely to have, can be eliminated by modification proposed by the parties or the Commission, as the case may be, under sub-section (7) of section 29 or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 29A, it may approve the combination subject to such modifications as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Where—`
  line
  line `(a) the Commission has directed under sub-section (2) that the combination shall not take effect; or`
  line
  line `(b) the parties to the combination, fail to carry out the modification within such period as may be specified by the Commission under sub-section (4); or`
  line
  line `(c) the Commission is of the opinion that the combination has, or is likely to have, an appreciable adverse effect on competition which cannot be eliminated by suitable modification to such combination,`
  line
  line `then, without prejudice to any penalty which may be imposed or any prosecution which may be initiated under this Act, the Commission may order that such combination shall not be given effect to, or be declared void, or frame a scheme to be implemented by the parties to address the appreciable adverse effect on competition, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) If no order is passed or direction issued by the Commission in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (5), as the case may be, within a period of one hundred and fifty days from the date of notice given to the Commission under sub-section (2) of section 6, the combination shall be deemed to have been approved by the Commission.]`
  line
  line `3* * * * *.`
  line
  line `(13) Where the Commission has ordered a combination to be void, the acquisition or acquiring of control or merger or amalgamation referred to in section 5, shall be dealt with by the authorities under any other law for the time being in force as if such acquisition or acquiring of control or merger or amalgamation had not taken place and the parties to the combination shall be dealt with accordingly.`
  line
  line `(14) Nothing contained in this Chapter shall affect any proceeding initiated or which may be initiated under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "certain" omitted by Act 9 of 2023, s. 23 (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `2. The words "including the combination" omitted by s. 23, ibid., (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for sub-sections (3), (4), (5) and (6) (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-sections (7), (8), (9), (10), (11) and (12) omitted by s. 23, ibid., (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (1162)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 35
  title `Acts taking place outside India but having an effect on competition in India`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1162&sectionno=32&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Commission shall, notwithstanding that,--`
  line
  line `(a) an agreement referred to in section 3 has been entered into outside India; or`
  line
  line `(b) any party to such agreement is outside India; or`
  line
  line `(c) any enterprise abusing the dominant position is outside India; or`
  line
  line `(d) a combination has taken place outside India; or`
  line
  line `(e) any party to combination is outside India; or`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter or practice or action arising out of such agreement or dominant position or`
  line `combination is outside India,`
  line
  line `have power to inquire ^1[in accordance with the provisions contained in sections 19, 20, 26, ^229, 29A and 30] of the Act into such agreement or abuse of dominant position or combination if such agreement or dominant position or combination has, or is likely to have, an appreciable adverse effect on competition in`
  line `the relevant market in India ^1[and pass such orders as it may deem fit in accordance with the provisions of this Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 25, (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 24, for "29 and 30" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (1163)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to issue interim orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 26, ibid., for section 33 (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1163&sectionno=33&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[33. Power to issue interim orders.--Where during an inquiry, the Commission is satisfied that an`
  line `act in contravention of sub-section (1) of section 3 or sub-section (1) of section 4 or section 6 has been`
  line `committed and continues to be committed or that such act is about to be committed, the Commission may,`
  line `by order, temporarily restrain any party from carrying on such act until the conclusion of such inquiry or`
  line `until further orders, without giving notice to such party, where it deems it necessary.]`
