obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (1165)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 38
  title `Appearance before Commission`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1165&sectionno=35&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[1] ^2[A party] or the Director General may either appear in`
  line `person or authorise one or more chartered accountants or company secretaries or cost accountants or legal`
  line `practitioners or any of his or its officers to present his or its case before the Commission.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "chartered accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) and who has`
  line `obtained a certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "company secretary" means a company secretary as defined in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980) and who has obtained a certificate of`
  line `practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "cost accountant" means a cost accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959) and who has obtained a`
  line `certificate of practice under sub- section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "legal practitioner" means an advocate, vakil or an attorney of any High Court, and includes a`
  line `pleader in practice.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), a party may call upon experts from the fields of economics,`
  line `commerce, international trade or from any other discipline to provide an expert opinion in connection`
  line `with any matter related to a case.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 35 shall be numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 9 of 2023, s. 25 (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for "A person or an enterprise" (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (1166)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of Commission to regulate its own procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for section 36 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1166&sectionno=36&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[36. Power of Commission to regulate its own procedure.-- (1) In the discharge of its functions,`
  line `the Commission shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of`
  line `this Act and of any rules made by the Central Government, the Commission shall have the powers to`
  line `regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a Civil Court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a`
  line `suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) requisitioning, subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act,`
  line `1872 (1 of 1872), any public record or document or copy of such record or document from any office.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may call upon such experts, from the fields of economics, commerce,`
  line `accountancy, international trade or from any other discipline as it deems necessary to assist the`
  line `Commission in the conduct of any inquiry by it.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission may direct any person--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce before the Director General or the Secretary or an officer authorised by it, such books, or other documents in the custody or under the control of such person so directed as may be specified or described in the direction, being documents relating to any trade, the examination of which may be required for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish to the Director General or the Secretary or any other officer authorised by it, as respects the trade or such other information as may be in his possession in relation to the trade carried on by such person, as may be required for the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (1167)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
