obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (1168)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 41
  title `Rectification of orders`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1168&sectionno=38&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, the`
  line `Commission may amend any order passed by it under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the Commission may make--`
  line
  line `(a) an amendment under sub-section (1) of its own motion;`
  line
  line `(b) an amendment for rectifying any such mistake which has been brought to its notice by any`
  line `party to the order.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the Commission shall not,`
  line `while rectifying any mistake apparent from record, amend substantive part of its order passed under`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (1169)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 42
  title `Execution of orders of Commission imposing monetary penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 31, for section 39 (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1169&sectionno=39&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[39. Execution of orders of Commission imposing monetary penalty.--(1) If a person fails to pay`
  line `any monetary penalty imposed on him under this Act, the Commission shall proceed to recover such`
  line `penalty, in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) In a case where the Commission is of the opinion that it would be expedient to recover the penalty`
  line `imposed under this Act in accordance with the provisions of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), it`
  line `may make a reference to this effect to the concerned income-tax authority under that Act for recovery of`
  line `the penalty as tax due under the said Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a reference has been made by the Commission under sub-section (2) for recovery of`
  line `penalty, the person upon whom the penalty has been imposed shall be deemed to be the assessee in`
  line `default under the Income Tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and the provisions contained in sections 221 to 227,`
  line `228A, 229, 231 and 232 of the said Act and the Second Schedule to that Act and any rules made there`
  line `under shall, in so far as may be, apply as if the said provisions were the provisions of this Act and referred`
  line `to sums by way of penalty imposed under this Act instead of to income- tax and sums imposed by way of`
  line `penalty, fine, and interest under the Incometax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and to the Commission instead of`
  line `the Assessing Officer.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--Any reference to sub-section (2) or sub-section (6) of section 220 of the income-tax`
  line `Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), in the said provisions of that Act or the rules made thereunder shall be construed`
  line `as references to sections 43 to 45 of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--The Tax Recovery Commissioner and the Tax Recovery Officer referred to in the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) shall be deemed to be the Tax Recovery Commissioner and the Tax`
  line `Recovery Officer for the purposes of recovery of sums imposed by way of penalty under this Act and`
  line `reference made by the Commission under sub-section (2) would amount to drawing of a certificate by the`
  line `Tax Recovery Officer as far as demand relating to penalty under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.--Any reference to appeal in Chapter XVIID and the Second Schedule to the Incometax`
  line `Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), shall be construed as a reference to appeal before the Competition Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under section 53B of this Act.]`
