obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (1171)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 44
  title `Director General to investigate contravention`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 33 (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1171&sectionno=41&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director General shall, when so`
  line `directed by the Commission, assist the Commission in investigating into any contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director General shall have all the powers as are conferred upon the Commission under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 36.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), sections 240 and 240A of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), so far as may be, shall apply to an investigation made by the Director General or`
  line `any other person investigating under his authority, as they apply to an inspector appointed under that Act.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the words "the Central Government" under section 240 of the Companies Act,1956`
  line `(1 of 1956) shall be construed as "the Commission";`
  line
  line `(b) the word "Magistrate" under section 240A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) shall be`
  line `construed as "the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Delhi".]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (1172)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 45
  title `Contravention of orders of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for section 42 (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1172&sectionno=42&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^1[42. Contravention of orders of Commission.--(1) The Commission may cause an inquiry to be`
  line `made into compliance of its orders or directions made in exercise of its powers under the Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person, without reasonable clause, fails to comply with the orders or directions of the`
  line `Commission issued under sections 27, 28, 31, 32, 33, 42A and 43A of the Act, he shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to rupees one lakh for each day during which such non-compliance occurs,`
  line `subject to a maximum of rupees ten crore, as the Commission may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person does not comply with the orders or directions issued, or fails to pay the fine imposed`
  line `under sub-section (2), he shall, without prejudice to any proceeding under section 39, be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which may extend to rupees`
  line `twenty-five crore, or with both, as the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Delhi may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Delhi shall not take cognizance of any offence under`
  line `this section save on a complaint filed by the Commission or any of its officers authorised by it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42_a:
  sectionId (1173)
  sectionNo 42A
  orderNo 46
  title `Compensation in case of contravention of orders of Commission`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1173&sectionno=42A&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_42_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[42A. Compensation in case of contravention of orders of Commission.--Without prejudice to`
  line `the provisions of this Act, any person may make an application to the Appellate Tribunal for an order for`
  line `the recovery of compensation from any enterprise for any loss or damage shown to have been suffered, by`
  line `such person as a result of the said enterprise violating directions issued by the Commission or`
  line `contravening, without any reasonable ground, any decision or order of the Commission issued ^2[under`
  line `sections 6, 27], 28, 31, 32 and 33 or any condition or restriction subject to which any approval, sanction,`
  line `direction or exemption in relation to any matter has been accorded, given, made or granted under this Act`
  line `or delaying in carrying out such orders or directions of the Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 28, for "under sections 27" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (1174)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 47
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with directions of Commission and Director General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 36, ibid., for section 43 (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1174&sectionno=43&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1[43. Penalty for failure to comply with directions of Commission and Director General.--If any`
  line `person fails to comply, without reasonable cause, with a direction given by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Commission under sub-sections (2) and (4) of section 36; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Director General while exercising powers referred to in sub-section (2) of section 41,`
  line `such person shall be punishable with fine which may extend to rupees one lakh for each day during which`
  line
  line `such failure continues subject to a maximum of rupees one crore, as may be determined by the`
  line Commission.]
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (1175)
  sectionNo 43A
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to impose penalty for non-furnishing of information on combinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 30, for section 43A (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1175&sectionno=43A&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[43A. Power to impose penalty for non-furnishing of information on combinations.--If any`
  line `person or enterprise fails to give notice to the Commission under sub-section (2) or sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 6 or contravenes sub-section (2A) of section 6 or submit information pursuant to an inquiry under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 20, the Commission may impose on such person or enterprise, a penalty which`
  line `may extend to one per cent., of the total turnover or assets or the value of transaction referred to in clause`
  line `(d) of section 5, whichever is higher, of such a combination:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case any person or enterprise has given a notice under sub-section (4) of section 6`
  line `and such notice is found to be void ab initio under sub-section (6) of section 6, then a notice under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 6 may be given by the acquirer or parties to the combination, as may be`
  line `applicable, within a period of thirty days of the order of the Commission under sub-section (6) of that`
  line `section and no action under this section shall be taken by the Commission till the expiry of such period of`
  line `thirty days.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (1176)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 49
  title `Penalty for making false statement or omission to furnish material information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1176&sectionno=44&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `person, being a party to a combination,--`
  line
  line `(a) makes a statement which is false in any material particular, or knowing it to be false; or`
  line
  line `(b) omits to state any material particular knowing it to be material,`
  line
  line `such person shall be liable to a penalty which shall not be less than rupees fifty lakhs but which may`
  line `extend to rupees one crore, as may be determined by the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (1177)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 50
  title `Penalty for contraventions in relation to furnishing of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 38, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 20-5-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1177&sectionno=45&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of section 44, if a person, who furnishes or is required to furnish under this Act any particulars,`
  line `documents or any information,--`
  line
  line `(a) makes any statement or furnishes any document which he knows or has reason to believe to`
  line `be false in any material particular; or`
  line
  line `(b) omits to state any material fact knowing it to be material; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully alters, suppresses or destroys any document which is required to be furnished as`
  line aforesaid,
  line
  line `such person shall be punishable with fine which may extend to rupees one crore as may be determined by`
  line `the Commission.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Commission may also pass such other`
  line `order as it deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (1178)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to impose lesser penalty`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 33, for section 46 (w.e.f. 20-2-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1178&sectionno=46&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `^1[46. Power to impose lesser penalty. (1) The Commission may, if it is satisfied that any producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider included in any cartel, which is alleged to have violated section 3, has made a full and true disclosure in respect of the alleged violations and such disclosure is`
  line `vital, impose upon such producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider a lesser penalty as may be specified by regulations, than leviable under this Act or the rules or the regulations made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that lesser penalty shall not be imposed by the Commission in cases where the report of investigation directed under section 26 has been received before making of such disclosure:`
  line
  line `Provided further that lesser penalty shall be imposed by the Commission only in respect of a producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider included in the cartel, who has made the full, true and vital disclosures under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided also that lesser penalty shall not be imposed by the Commission if the person making the disclosure does not continue to co-operate with the Commission till the completion of the proceedings before the Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Commission may, if it is satisfied that such producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider included in the cartel had in the course of proceedings,--`
  line
  line `(a) not complied with the condition on which the lesser penalty was imposed by the`
  line `Commission; or`
  line
  line `(b) had given false evidence; or`
  line
  line `(c) the disclosure made is not vital,`
  line
  line `and thereupon such producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider may be tried for the contravention with respect to which the lesser penalty was imposed and shall also be liable to the imposition of penalty to which such person has been liable, had lesser penalty not been imposed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may allow a producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider included in the cartel, to withdraw its application for lesser penalty under this section, in such manner and within such time as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Director General and the Commission shall be entitled to use for the purposes of this Act, any evidence submitted by a producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider in its application for lesser penalty, except its admission.`
  line
  line `(4) Where during the course of the investigation, a producer, seller, distributor, trader or service`
  line `provider who has disclosed a cartel under sub-section (1), makes a full, true and vital disclosure under`
  line `sub-section (1) with respect to another cartel in which it is alleged to have violated section 3, which enables the Commission to form a prima facie opinion under sub-section (1) of section 26 that there exists`
  line `another cartel, then the Commission may impose upon such producer, seller, distributor, trader or service`
  line `provider a lesser penalty as may be specified by regulations, in respect of the cartel already being`
  line `investigated, without prejudice to the producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider obtaining`
  line `lesser penalty under sub-section (1) regarding the newly disclosed cartel.]`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (1179)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 52
  title `Crediting sums realised by way of penalties to Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 34, (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1179&sectionno=47&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `All sums`
  line `realised by way of penalties ^1[and recovery of legal costs by the Commission] under this Act shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (1180)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 53
  title `Contravention by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 35, for section 48 (w.e.f. 6-3-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1180&sectionno=48&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `^1[48. Contravention by companies.]--(1) Where a person committing contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule, regulation, order made or direction issued thereunder is a company, every person who, at the time the contravention was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be in contravention of this Act and unless otherwise provided in this Act, the Commission may impose such penalty on such persons, as it may deem fit which shall not be more than ten per cent. of the average of the income for the last three preceding financial years:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case any agreement referred to in sub-section (3) of section 3 has been entered into by a cartel, the Commission may unless otherwise provided in this Act, impose upon such persons referred to in sub-section (1), a penalty of up to ten per cent. of the income for each year of the continuance of such agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall render any such person liable to any penalty if he proves that the contravention was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such contravention.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where a contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule, regulation, order made or direction issued thereunder has been committed by a company and it is proved that the contravention has taken place with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officers of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officers shall also be deemed to be in contravention of the provisions of this Act and unless otherwise provided in this Act, the Commission may impose such penalty on such persons, as it may deem fit which shall not be more than ten per cent. of the average of the income for the last three preceding financial years:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case any agreement referred to in sub-section (3) of section 3 has been entered into`
  line `by a cartel, the Commission may, unless otherwise provided under this Act, impose upon such person a`
  line `penalty as it may deem fit which shall not exceed ten per cent. of the income for each year of the`
  line `continuance of such agreement.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm;`
  line
  line `(c) "income", in relation to a person, shall be determined in such manner as may be specified by regulations].`
obj_root_law_sections_48_a:
  sectionId (87114)
  sectionNo 48A
  orderNo 54
  title Settlement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 35, for section 48 (w.e.f. 6-3-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=87114&sectionno=48A&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_48_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[48A. Settlement.--(1) Any enterprise, against whom any inquiry has been initiated under sub-section (1) of section 26 for contravention of sub-section (4) of section 3 or section 4, may, for settlement of the proceeding initiated for the alleged contraventions, submit an application in writing to the Commission in such form and upon payment of such fee as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) may be submitted at any time after the receipt of the report of the Director General under sub-section (4) of section 26 but prior to such time before the passing of an order under section 27 or section 28 as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may, after taking into consideration the nature, gravity and impact of the contraventions, agree to the proposal for settlement, on payment of such amount by the applicant or on such other terms and manner of implementation of settlement and monitoring as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) While considering the proposal for settlement, the Commission shall provide an opportunity to the party concerned, the Director General, or any other party to submit their objections and suggestions, if any.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Commission is of the opinion that the settlement offered under sub-section (1) is not appropriate in the circumstances or if the Commission and the party concerned do not reach an agreement on the terms of the settlement within such time as may be specified by regulations, it shall, by order, reject the settlement application and proceed with its inquiry under section 26.`
  line
  line `(6) The procedure for conducting the settlement proceedings under this section shall be such as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(7) No appeal shall lie under section 53B against any order passed by the Commission under this section.`
  line
  line `(8) All settlement amounts, realised under this Act shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_b:
  sectionId (87115)
  sectionNo 48B
  orderNo 55
  title Commitment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=87115&sectionno=48B&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_48_b_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48_c:
  sectionId (87116)
  sectionNo 48C
  orderNo 56
  title `Revocation of the Settlement or Commitment order and penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 35, for section 48 (w.e.f. 6-3-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=87116&sectionno=48C&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_48_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[48C. Revocation of the settlement or commitment order and penalty.--If an applicant fails to comply with the order passed under section 48A or section 48B or it comes to the notice of the Commission that the applicant has not made full and true disclosure or there has been a material change in the facts, the order passed under section 48A or section 48B, as the case may be, shall stand revoked and`
  line `withdrawn and such enterprise shall be liable to pay legal costs incurred by the Commission which may extend to rupees one crore and the Commission may restore or initiate the inquiry in respect of which the order under section 48A or section 48B was passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (1181)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 57
  title `Competition advocacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1181&sectionno=49&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Central Government may, in formulating a policy on`
  line `competition (including review of laws related to competition) or any other matter, and a State`
  line `Government may, in formulating a policy on competition or on any other matter, as the case may be,`
  line `make a reference to the Commission for its opinion on possible effect of such policy on competition and`
  line `on the receipt of such a reference, the Commission shall, within sixty days of making such reference, give`
  line `its opinion to the Central Government, or the State Government, as the case may be, which may thereafter`
  line `take further action as it deems fit.]`
  line
  line `(2) The opinion given by the Commission under sub-section (1) shall not be binding upon the Central`
  line `Government ^2[or the State Government, as the case may be,] in formulating such policy.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall take suitable measures ^3*** for the promotion of competition advocacy,`
  line `creating awareness and imparting training about competition issues.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 40, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `3. The words ", as may be prescribed," omitted by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (1182)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 58
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1182&sectionno=50&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Commission grants of such sums of money as the`
  line `Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (1183)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 59
  title `Constitution of Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1183&sectionno=51&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a fund to be called the "Competition`
  line `Fund" and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) all Government grants received by the Commission;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) the fees received under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the interest accrued on the amounts referred to in ^2[clauses (a) and (c).]`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and other Members and the administrative expenses including the salaries, allowances and pension payable to the Director General, Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors General, the Registrar and officers and other employees of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) the other expenses of the Commission in connection with the discharge of its functions and for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be administered by a committee of such Members of the Commission as may be determined by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(4) The committee appointed under sub-section (3) shall spend monies out of the Fund for carrying out the objects for which the Fund has been constituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Cl. (b) omitted by Act 39 of 2007, s. 41 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 41, ibid., for "clauses (a) to (c)" (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (1184)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 60
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 42, ibid., for "Supreme Court" (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1184&sectionno=52&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the orders of the Commission,`
  line `being matters appealable to the ^1[Appellate Tribunal or the Supreme Court], shall not be subject to audit`
  line `under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Commission shall have the same rights, privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has, in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Commission as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (1185)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 61
  title `Furnishing of returns, etc., to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1185&sectionno=53&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall furnish to the`
  line `Central Government at such time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central`
  line `Government may direct, such returns and statements and such particulars in regard to any proposed or`
  line `existing measures for the promotion of competition advocacy, creating awareness and imparting training`
  line `about competition issues, as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall prepare once in every year, in such form and at such time as may be`
  line `prescribed, an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during the previous year and`
  line `copies of the report shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53_a:
  sectionId (1186)
  sectionNo 53A
  orderNo 62
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1186&sectionno=53A&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[ ^3[ ^4[53A. Appellate Tribunal.-- The National Company Law Appellate Tribunal constituted under`
  line `section 410 of the Companies Act, 2013 ( 18 of 2013) shall, on and from the commencement of Part XIV`
  line `of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), be the Appellate Tribunal for the purposes of this Act`
  line `and the said Appellate Tribunal shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hear and dispose of appeals against any direction issued or decision made or order passed by`
  line `the Commission under ^5[sub-section (6) of section 6, sub-sections (2), (2A), (6) and (9) of section 26],`
  line `section 27, section 28, section 31, section 32, section 33, section 38, section 39, section 43, section`
  line `43A, section 44, section 45 or section 46 of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) adjudicate on claim for compensation that may arise from the findings of the Commission or`
  line `the orders of the Appellate Tribunal in an appeal against any finding of the Commission or under`
  line `section 42A or under sub-section (2) of section 53Q of this Act, and pass orders for the recovery of`
  line `compensation under section 53N of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 171, for the heading (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `3. 12-10-2007, vide S.O. No. 1747(E), dated 12-10-2007.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 171, for section 53A (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 38, for "sub-sections (2) and (6) of section 26" (w.e.f. 10-9-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_b:
  sectionId (1187)
  sectionNo 53B
  orderNo 63
  title `Appeal to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1187&sectionno=53B&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[^253B. Appeal to Appellate Tribunal.-- (1) The Central Government or the State Government or a`
  line `local authority or enterprise or any person, aggrieved by any direction, decision or order referred to in`
  line `clause (a) of section 53A may prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of sixty days from the date on`
  line `which a copy of the direction or decision or order made by the Commission is received by the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government or a local authority or enterprise or any person referred to in that`
  line `sub-section and it shall be in such form and be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `sixty days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties`
  line `to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or setting aside the direction, decision or order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the Commission and the`
  line `parties to the appeal.`
  line
  line `(5) The appeal filed before the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by it as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal within six months`
  line `from the date of receipt of the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009.`
