obj_root_law_sections_53_n:
  sectionId (1199)
  sectionNo 53N
  orderNo 75
  title `Awarding compensation`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_n_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_n_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1199&sectionno=53N&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_n_content:
  string
  line `^153N. Awarding compensation.(1) Without prejudice to any other provisions contained in this Act, the Central Government or a State Government or a local authority or any enterprise or any person may make an application to the Appellate Tribunal to adjudicate on claim for compensation that may arise from the findings of the Commission or the orders of the Appellate Tribunal in an appeal against any findings of the Commission or under section 42A or ^2[ under sub-section (2) of section 53Q or the orders of the Supreme Court in an appeal against the findings of the Appellate Tribunal under section 53T or an order for settlement passed under section 48A, and to pass an order for the recovery of compensation from any enterprise for any loss or damage shown to have been suffered, by the Central Government or a State Government or a local authority or any enterprise or any person as a result of any contravention of the provisions of Chapter II, having been committed by enterprise or as a result of order of settlement passed by the Commission].`
  line
  line `(2) Every application made under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by the findings of the Commission ^3[or Appellate Tribunal or the Supreme Court, or an order for settlement], if any, and also be accompanied with such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appellate Tribunal may, after an inquiry made into the allegations mentioned in the`
  line `application made under sub-section (1), pass an order directing the enterprise to make payment to the`
  line `applicant, of the amount determined by it as realisable from the enterprise as compensation for the loss or`
  line `damage caused to the applicant as a result of any contravention of the provisions of Chapter II having`
  line `been committed by such enterprise:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may obtain the recommendations of the Commission before`
  line `passing an order of compensation.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any loss or damage referred to in sub-section (1) is caused to numerous persons having the`
  line `same interest, one or more of such persons may, with the permission of the Appellate Tribunal, make an`
  line `application under that sub-section for and on behalf of, or for the benefit of, the persons so interested, and`
  line `thereupon, the provisions of rule 8 of Order 1 of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), shall apply subject to the modification that every reference therein to a suit or decree shall be`
  line `construed as a reference to the application before the Appellate Tribunal and the order of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal thereon.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that--`
  line
  line `(a) (a) an application may be made for compensation before the Appellate Tribunal only after either the Commission or the Appellate Tribunal on appeal under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 53A ^1[or the Supreme Court on appeal under section 53T] of the Act, has determined in a proceeding before it that violation of the provisions of the Act has taken place, or if provisions of section 42A or sub-section (2) of section 53Q of the Act are attracted;`
  line
  line `(b) enquiry to be conducted under sub-section (3) shall be for the purpose of determining the eligibility and quantum of compensation due to a person applying for the same, and not for examining afresh the findings of the Commission or the Appellate Tribunal ^1[or the Supreme Court,] on whether any violation of the Act has taken place`
obj_root_law_sections_53_n_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No. 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009.`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 40, for certain words (w.e.f. 6-3-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 40, ibid (w.e.f. 6-3-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_o:
  sectionId (1200)
  sectionNo 53O
  orderNo 76
  title `Procedures and powers of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_o_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_o_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1200&sectionno=53O&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[^253-O. Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Appellate Tribunal shall not be`
  line `bound by the procedure laid down in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided`
  line `by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act and of any rules made`
  line `by the Central Government, the Appellate Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own procedure`
  line `including the places at which they shall have their sittings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while`
  line `trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872`
  line `(1 of 1872), requisitioning any public record or document or copy of such record or document from`
  line `any office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(g) dismissing a representation for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) setting aside any order of dismissal of any representation for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceedings before the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings`
  line `within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) and the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195`
  line `and Chapter XXVI of the Code or Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_o_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No. 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_p:
  sectionId (1201)
  sectionNo 53P
  orderNo 77
  title `Execution of orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_p_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_p_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1201&sectionno=53P&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[^253P. Execution of orders of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) Every order made by the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall be enforced by it in the same manner as if it were a decree made by a court in a suit pending therein,`
  line `and it shall be lawful for the Appellate Tribunal to send, in case of its inability to execute such order, to`
  line `the court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an order against a company, the registered office of the company is situated; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an order against any other person, place where the person concerned voluntarily resides or carries on business or personally works for gain, is situated.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may transmit any order made by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if it were a decree made by that court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_p_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No. 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009`
obj_root_law_sections_53_q:
  sectionId (1202)
  sectionNo 53Q
  orderNo 78
  title `Contravention of orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_q_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_q_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1202&sectionno=53Q&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_q_content:
  string
  line `^1[^253Q. Contravention of orders of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, if any person contravenes, without any reasonable ground, any order of the Appellate Tribunal,`
  line `he shall be liable for a penalty of not exceeding rupees one crore or imprisonment for a term up to three`
  line `years or with both as the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Delhi may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Delhi shall not take cognizance of any offence`
  line `punishable under this sub-section, save on a complaint made by an officer authorised by the Appellate`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of this Act, any person may make an application to the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal for an order for the recovery of compensation from any enterprise for any loss or`
  line `damage shown to have been suffered, by such person as a result of the said enterprise contravening,`
  line `without any reasonable ground, any order of the Appellate Tribunal or delaying in carrying out such`
  line `orders of the Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_q_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No. 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_r:
  sectionId (1203)
  sectionNo 53R
