  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_r_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_r_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1203&sectionno=53R&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_r_content:
  string
  line `^1[^253R. [Vacancy in Appellate Tribunal not to invalidate acts or proceedings.] Omitted by s. 171,`
  line `ibid. (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_r_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No. 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_s:
  sectionId (1204)
  sectionNo 53S
  orderNo 80
  title `Right to legal representation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_s_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_s_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1204&sectionno=53S&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_s_content:
  string
  line `^1[^253-S. Right to legal representation.-- (1) A person preferring an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `may either appear in person or authorise one or more chartered accountants or company secretaries or cost`
  line `accountants or legal practitioners or any of its officers to present his or its case before the Appellate`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or a State Government or a local authority or any enterprise preferring`
  line `an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal may authorise one or more chartered accountants or company`
  line `secretaries or cost accountants or legal practitioners or any of its officers to act as presenting officers and`
  line `every person so authorised may present the case with respect to any appeal before the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may authorise one or more chartered accountants or company secretaries or cost`
  line `accountants or legal practitioners or any of its officers to act as presenting officers and every person so`
  line `authorised may present the case with respect to any appeal before the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The expressions "chartered accountant" or "company secretary" or "cost accountant"`
  line `or "legal practitioner" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Explanation to section 35.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_s_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No. 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_t:
  sectionId (1205)
  sectionNo 53T
  orderNo 81
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_t_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_t_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1205&sectionno=53T&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_t_content:
  string
  line `^1[^253T. Appeal to Supreme Court.--The Central Government or any State Government or the`
  line `Commission or any statutory authority or any local authority or any enterprise or any person aggrieved by`
  line `any decision or order of the Appellate Tribunal may file an appeal to the Supreme Court within sixty days`
  line `from the date of communication of the decision or order of the Appellate Tribunal to them:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme court may, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed after the expiry of the said period`
  line `of sixty days.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_t_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No. 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_u:
  sectionId (1206)
  sectionNo 53U
  orderNo 82
  title `Power to Punish for contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_u_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_u_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1206&sectionno=53U&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_53_u_content:
  string
  line `^1[^253U. Power to Punish for contempt.--The Appellate Tribunal shall have, and exercise, the same`
  line `jurisdiction, powers and authority in respect of contempt of itself as a High Court has and may exercise`
  line `and, for this purpose, the provisions of the Contempt of Courts Act, 1971 (70 of 1971) shall have effect`
  line `subject to modifications that,--`
  line
  line `(a) the reference therein to a High Court shall be construed as including a reference to the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) the references to the Advocate-General in section 15 of the said Act shall be construed as a reference to such Law Officer as the Central Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_u_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 43 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `2. 20-5-2009, vide S.O. No. 1242(E), dated 15-5-2009.`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (1207)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 83
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1207&sectionno=54&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, exempt from the application`
  line `of this Act, or any provision thereof, and for such period as it may specify in such notification--`
  line
  line `(a) any class of enterprises if such exemption is necessary in the interest of security of the State or`
  line `public interest;`
  line
  line `(b) any practice or agreement arising out of and in accordance with any obligation assumed by`
  line `India under any treaty, agreement or convention with any other country or countries;`
  line
  line `(c) any enterprise which performs a sovereign function on behalf of the Central Government or a`
  line `State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case an enterprise is engaged in any activity including the activity relatable to the`
  line `sovereign functions of the Government, the Central Government may grant exemption only in respect`
  line `of activity relatable to the sovereign functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (1208)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 84
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1208&sectionno=55&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Commission shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its functions`
  line `under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy, other than those relating to technical`
  line `and administrative matters, as the Central Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commission shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (1209)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1209&sectionno=56&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the Central`
  line `Government is of the opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of circumstances beyond the control of the Commission, it is unable to`
  line `discharge the functions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Commission has persistently made default in complying with any direction given by`
  line `the Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions or performance of the`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default the financial`
  line `position of the Commission or the administration of the Commission has suffered; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by notification and for reasons to be specified therein, supersede the`
  line `Commission for such period, not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Commission to make representations against the proposed supersession and shall`
  line `consider representations, if any, of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Commission,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson and other Members shall as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices`
  line `as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Commission shall, until the Commission is`
  line `reconstituted under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by the Central Government or such`
  line `authority as the Central Government may specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all properties owned or controlled by the Commission shall, until the Commission is`
  line `reconstituted under sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On or before the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall reconstitute the Commission by a fresh appointment of its Chairperson and other Members and in such case any person who had vacated his office under clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed to be disqualified for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before each House of Parliament at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (1210)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 86
  title `Restriction on disclosure of information`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 44, for "the Commission" (w.e.f. 12-10-2007)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1210&sectionno=57&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `No information relating to any enterprise, being an`
  line `information which has been obtained by or on behalf of ^1[the Commission or the Appellate Tribunal] for`
  line `the purposes of this Act, shall, without the previous permission in writing of the enterprise, be disclosed`
  line `otherwise than in compliance with or for the purposes of this Act or any other law for the time being in`
  line force.
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (1211)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 87
  title `Chairperson, Members, Director General, Secretary, officers and other employees, etc., to be public servants`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for section 58 (w.e.f. (12-10-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1211&sectionno=58&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `^1[58. Chairperson, Members, Director General, Secretary, officers and other employees, etc., to`
  line `be public servants.--The Chairperson and other Members and the Director General, Additional, Joint,`
  line `Deputy or Assistant Directors General and Secretary and officers and other employees of the Commission`
  line `and the Chairperson, Members, officers and other employees of the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed,`
  line `while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (1212)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 88
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 46, for "Registrar or officers or other employees of the Commission" (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1212&sectionno=59&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or Commission or any officer of the Central Government or the`
  line `Chairperson or any Member or the Director- General, Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors`
  line `General or ^1[the Secretary or officers or other employees of the Commission or the Chairperson,`
  line `Members, officers and other employees of the Appellate Tribunal] for anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_a:
  sectionId (74280)
  sectionNo 59A
  orderNo 89
  title `Compounding of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 42 (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=74280&sectionno=59A&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_59_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[59A. Compounding of certain offences.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence punishable under this Act, not being an offence`
  line `punishable with imprisonment only or imprisonment and also with fine, may either before or after the`
  line `institution of any proceeding, be compounded by the Appellate Tribunal or a court before which such`
  line `proceeding is pending.]`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (1213)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 90
  title `Act to have overriding effect`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1213&sectionno=60&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (1214)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 91
  title `Exclusion of jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 47, ibid., for "Commission" (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1214&sectionno=61&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any`
  line `suit or proceeding in respect of any matter which the^1[Commission or the Appellate Tribunal] is`
  line `empowered by or under this Act to determine and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other`
  line `authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (1215)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 92
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1215&sectionno=62&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (1216)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 93
  title `Power to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1216&sectionno=63&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the value of the assets or turnover of the enterprise acquired, taken control of, merged or`
  line `amalgamated in India under clause (e) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(ab) the percentage of voting rights higher than twenty-six per cent. under sub-clause (i) of clause`
  line `(b) of the Explanation to section 5;`
  line
  line `(ac) the criteria of combinations under sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(ad) the criteria under sub-section (7) of section 6;]`
  line
  line ^2[
  line `^3[(ae)] the term of the Selection Committee and the manner of selection of panel of names`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 9;]`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which and the authorit`
  line `y before whom the oath of office and of secrecy`
  line `shall be made and subscribed to under sub-section (3) of section 10;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) the salary and the other terms and conditions of service including travelling expenses, house`
  line `rent allowance and conveyance facilities, sumptuary allowance and medical facilities to be provided`
  line `to the Chairperson and other Members under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `^5[(da) the number of Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors General or such officers or`
  line `other employees in the office of Director General and the manner in which such Additional, Joint,`
  line `Deputy or Assistant Directors General or such officers or other employees may be appointed under`
  line `sub- section (1A) of section 16;]`
  line
  line `(e) the salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Director General,`
  line `Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors General or ^6[such officers or other employees] under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section16;`
  line
  line `(f) the qualifications for appointment of the Director General, Additional, Joint, Deputy or`
  line `Assistant Directors General or ^10[such officers or other employees] under sub-section (4) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(g) the salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the ^7[Secretary] and`
  line `officers and other employees payable, and the number of such officers and employees under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section17;`
  line
  line `^8 * * * *`
  line
  line `(k) the form in which the annual statement of accounts shall be prepared under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 52;`
  line
  line `(l) the time within which and the form and manner in which the Commission may furnish returns,`
  line `statements and such particulars as the Central Government may require under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 53;`
  line
  line `(m) the form in which and the time within which the annual report shall be prepared under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 53;`
  line
  line `^9[(ma) the form in which an appeal may be filed before the Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 53B and the fees payable in respect of such appeal;`
  line
  line `^10 * * * *`
  line
  line `(me) the fee which shall be accompanied with every application made under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 53N;`
  line
  line `(mf) the other matters under clause (i) of sub-section (2) of section 53-O in respect of which the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall have powers under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while`
  line `trying a suit;]`
  line
  line `^11[(mg) the form of the publication of guidelines under sub-section (5) of section 64B;]`
  line
  line `^12[(n) the manner in which the monies transferred to the Competition Commission of India or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall be dealt with by the Commission or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may`
  line `be, under the fourth proviso to sub-section (2) of section 66;]`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be, or may be, made by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every notification issued under sub-section (3) of section 20 and section 54 and every rule made`
  line `under this Act by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session, or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the notification or rule, or both Houses agree that the notification should not be issued or rule should`
  line `not be made, the notification or rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that notification or rule, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 43 (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 48, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (a) re-lettered as clause (ae) thereof by Act 9 of 2023, s. 43 (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  line
  line `4 Cl. (c) omitted by Act 39 of 2007, s. 48 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 48 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 48, ibid., for "such other advisers, consultants or officers" (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 48, ibid., for "Registrar" (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `8. Cls. (h), (i) and (j) omitted by s. 48, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by s. 48 (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
  line
  line `10. Clauses (mb), (mc) and (md) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 171 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 43 (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 48, for clause (n) (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (1217)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 94
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1217&sectionno=64&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may, by notification, make regulations`
  line `consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the cost of production to be determined under clause (b) of the Explanation to section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the form of notice as may be specified and the fee which may be determined under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) the manner of determination of substantial business operations in India under clause (d) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(ca) the form and fee for notice for combination under sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(cb) the time and manner for filing notice of acquisition under clause (a) of section 6A;`
  line
  line `(cc) the manner and circumstance in which the acquirer may exercise the ownership or beneficial`
  line `right or interest in shares or convertible securities including voting right and receipt of dividends or`
  line `any other distributions as an exception under clause (b) of section 6A;]`
  line
  line `^2[(d) the procedures to be followed for engaging the experts and professionals under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(e) the fee which may be determined under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(f) the rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at the meetings of the`
  line `Commission under sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `^1[(fa) other details to be indicated in the show-cause notice under sub-section (9) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(fb) the manner of determining turnover or income under theExplanation I to clause (b) of`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `(fc) the manner in which modification may be proposed by parties to the combination to the`
  line `Commission under sub-section (2) of section 29A;]`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which penalty shall be recovered under sub-section (1) of section 39;`
  line
  line `^1[(ga) the lesser penalty to be imposed on producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(gb) the manner and time for withdrawal of application for lesser penalty under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 46;`
  line
  line `(gc) the lesser penalty to be imposed on producer, seller, distributor, trader or service provider`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(gd) the manner of determining income under clause (c) of Explanation to section 48;`
  line
  line `(ge) the form of application and fee under sub-section (1), the time under sub-section (2), the`
  line `terms and manner of implementations and monitoring under sub-section (3) and the procedure for`
  line `conducting settlement proceedings under sub-section (6) of section 48A;`
  line
  line `(gf) the form of application and fee under sub-section (1), the time under sub-section (2), the`
  line `terms and manner of implementations and monitoring under sub-section (3) and the procedure for`
  line `commitments offered under sub-section (6) of section 48B;`
  line
  line `(gg) the other details to be published along with draft regulations and the period for inviting`
  line `public comments under clause (a) of section 64A;]`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter in respect of which provision is to be, or may be, made by regulations.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation, or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 44, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 49, for clauses (d) and (e) (w.e.f. 12-10-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_a:
  sectionId (74281)
  sectionNo 64A
  orderNo 95
  title `Process of issuing regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2023, s. 45 (w.e.f. 18-5-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=74281&sectionno=64A&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_64_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[64A. Process of issuing regulations.--The Commission shall ensure transparency while making`
  line `regulations under section 64, by--`
  line
  line `(a) publishing draft regulations along with such other details as may be specified on its website`
  line `and inviting public comments for a specified period prior to issuing regulations;`
  line
  line `(b) publishing a general statement of its response to the public comments, not later than the date`
  line `of notification of the regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) periodically reviewing such regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Commission is of the opinion that certain regulations are required to be made or`
  line `existing regulations are required to be amended urgently in public interest or the subject matter of the`
  line `regulation relates solely to the internal functioning of the Commission, it may make regulations or amend`
  line `the existing regulations, as the case may be, without following the provisions stated in this section`
  line `recording the reason, for doing so.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_b:
  sectionId (79483)
  sectionNo 64B
  orderNo 96
  title `Commission to issue guidelines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 45, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=79483&sectionno=64B&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_64_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[64B. Commission to issue guidelines.-- (1) The Commission may publish guidelines on`
  line `the provisions of this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder either on a request made`
  line `by a person or on its own motion.`
  line
  line `(2) Guidelines issued under sub-section (1) shall not be construed as determination of any`
  line `question of fact or law by the Commission, its Members or officers and shall not be binding`
  line `on the Commission, its Members or officers.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to anything contained in sub-section (1), the Commission shall`
  line `publish guidelines as to the appropriate amount of any penalty for any contravention of`
  line `provision of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) While imposing penalty under clause (b) of section 27 or under section 43A or section`
  line `48 for any contravention of provision of this Act, the Commission shall consider the`
  line `guidelines under sub-section (3) and provide reasons in case of any divergence from such`
  line guidelines.
  line
  line `(5) The guidelines under sub-sections (1) and (3) shall be published in such form as may`
  line `be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (1218)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 97
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1218&sectionno=65&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years`
  line `from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (1219)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 98
  title `Repeal and saving`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781&sectionId=1219&sectionno=66&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00005_200312_1517807324781
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Act, 1969`
  line `(54 of 1969) is hereby repealed and the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission`
  line `established under sub-section (1) of section 5 of the said Act (hereafter referred to as the repealed Act)`
  line `shall stand dissolved.`
  line
  line `^2 ** * * *`
  line *
  line
  line `(1A) The repeal of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Act, 1969 (54 of 1969) shall, however, not affect,--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of the Act so repealed or anything duly done or suffered thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the Act so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, confiscation or punishment incurred in respect of any contravention under the Act so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(d) any proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege, obligation, liability, penalty, confiscation or punishment as aforesaid, and any such proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced, and any such penalty, confiscation or punishment may be imposed or made as if that Act had not been repealed.]`
  line
  line `(2) On the dissolution of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission, the person appointed as the Chairman of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission and every other person appointed as Member and Director General of Investigation and Registration, Additional, Joint, Deputy, or Assistant Directors General of Investigation and Registration and any officer and other employee of that Commission and holding office as such immediately before such dissolution shall vacate their respective offices and such Chairman and other Members shall be entitled to claim compensation not exceeding three months pay and allowances for the premature termination of term of their office or of any contract of service:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Director General of Investigation and Registration, Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors General of Investigation and Registration or any officer or other employee who has been, immediately before the dissolution of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission appointed on deputation basis to the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission, shall, on such dissolution, stand reverted to his parent cadre, Ministry or Department, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that the Director General of Investigation and Registration, Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors General of Investigation and Registration or any officer or other employee who has been, immediately before the dissolution of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission employed on regular basis by the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission, shall become, on and from such dissolution, the officer and employee, respectively, of the Competition Commission of India or the Appellate Tribunal, in such manner as may be specified by the Central Government, with the same rights and privileges as to pension, gratuity and other like matters as would have been admissible to him if the rights in relation to such Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission had not been transferred to, and vested in, the Competition Commission of India or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment in the Competition Commission of India or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, is duly terminated or until his remuneration, terms and conditions of employment are duly altered by the Competition Commission of India or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be:]`
  line
  line `Provided also that notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any Director General of Investigation and Registration, Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors General of Investigation and Registration or any officer or other employee, employed in the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission, to ^4[the Competition Commission of India or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be,] shall not entitle such Director General of Investigation and Registration, Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors General of Investigation and Registration or any officer or other employee any compensation under this Act or any other law for the time being in force and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission has established a provident fund, superannuation, welfare or other fund for the benefit of the Director General of Investigation and Registration, Additional, Joint, Deputy or Assistant Directors General of Investigation	and Registration or the officers and other employees employed in the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission, the monies relatable to the officers and other employees whose services have been transferred by or under this Act to ^5[the Competition Commission of India or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, shall, out of the monies standing], on the dissolution of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission to the credit of such provident fund, superannuation, welfare or other fund, stand transferred to, and vest in, ^6[the Competition Commission of India or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, and such monies which stand so transferred shall be dealt with by the said Commission or the Tribunal, as the case may be, in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^7[(3) All cases pertaining to monopolistic trade practices or restrictive trade practices pending (including such cases, in which any unfair trade practice has also been alleged), before the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission shall, ^8[on the commencement of the Competition Amendment Act, 2009 (39 of 2009)] stand transferred to the Appellate Tribunal and shall be adjudicated by the Appellate Tribunal in accordance with the provisions of the repealed Act as if that Act had not been repealed.`
  line
  line `^9[Explanation--.For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that all cases referred to in this sub-section, sub-section (4) and sub-section (5) shall be deemed to include all applications made for the losses or damages under section 12B of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Act,1969 (54 of 1969) as it stood before its repeal.]`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), all cases pertaining to unfair trade practices other than those referred to in clause (x) of sub-section (1) of section 36A of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Act, 1969 (54 of 1969) and pending before the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission ^10[immediately before the commencement of the Competition (Amendment) Act, 2009 (39 of 2009), shall, on such commencement], stand transferred to the National Commission constituted under the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986) and the National Commission shall dispose of such cases as if they were cases filed under that Act: Provided that the National Commission may, if it considers appropriate, transfer any case transferred to it under this sub-section, to the concerned State Commission established under section 9 of the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986) and that State Commission shall dispose of such case as if it was filed under that Act:`
  line
  line `^11[Provided further that all the cases relating to the unfair trade practices pending, before the National Commission under this sub-section, on or before the date on which the Competition (Amendment) Bill, 2009 receives the assent of the President, shall, on and from that date, stand transferred to the Appellate Tribunal and be adjudicated by the Appellate Tribunal in accordance with the provisions of the repealed Act as if that Act had not been repealed.]`
  line
  line `^12[(5) All cases pertaining to unfair trade practices referred to in clause (x) of sub-section (1) of section 36A of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Act, 1969 (54 of 1969) and pending before the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission shall, ^13[on the commencement of the Competition (Amendment) Act, 2009 (39 of 2009)], stand transferred to the Appellate Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall dispose of such cases as if they were cases filed under that Act.]`
  line
  line `(6) All investigations or proceedings, other than those relating to unfair trade practices, pending before the Director General of Investigation and Registration on or before the commencement of this Act shall, on such commencement, stand transferred to the Competition Commission of India, and the Competition Commission of India may conduct or order for conduct of such investigation or proceedings in the manner as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(7) All investigations or proceedings, relating to unfair trade practices, other than those referred to in clause (x) of sub-section (1) of section 36A of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Act, 1969 (54 of 1969) and pending before the Director General of Investigation and Registration on or before the commencement of this Act shall, on such commencement, stand transferred to the National Commission constituted under the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986) and the National Commission may conduct or order for conduct of such investigation or proceedings in the manner as it deems fit:`
  line
  line `^14[Provided that all investigations or proceedings, relating to unfair trade practices pending before the National Commission, on or before the date on which the Competition (Amendment) Bill, 2009 receives the assent of the President shall, on and from that date, stand transferred to the Appellate Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal may conduct or order for conduct of such investigation or proceedings in the manner as it deems fit.]`
  line
  line `(8) All investigations or proceedings relating to unfair trade practices referred to in clause (x) of sub-section (1) of section 36A of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Act, 1969 (54 of 1969), and pending before the Director General of Investigation and Registration on or before the commencement of this Act shall, on such commencement, stand transferred to the Competition Commission of India and the Competition Commission of India may conduct or order for conduct of such investigation in the manner as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(9) Save as otherwise provided under sub-sections (3) to (8), all cases or proceedings pending before the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission shall abate.`
  line
  line `(10) The mention of the particular matters referred to in sub-sections (3) to (8) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 50, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-2009).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso and the Explanation omitted by Act 39 of 2009, s. 2 (w.e.f. 14-10-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 50, for the second proviso (w.e.f. 1-9-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 39 of 2007, s. 50, for the Central Government (w.e.f. 1-9-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for the Central Government shall, out of the monies standing (w.e.f. 1-9-2009).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-9-2009).`
  line
  line `7.Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-9-2009)..`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 39 of 2009, s. 2, for after the expiry of two years referred to in the proviso to sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-10-2009).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-10-2009).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for on or before the expiry of two years referred to in the proviso to sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-10-2009).`
  line
  line `11.The proviso inserted by Act 39 of 2009, s. 2 (w.e.f.14-10-2009).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by s. 50, @@ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 1-9-2009).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 39 of 2009, s. 2, for certain words (date to be notified).`
  line
  line `14.The proviso ins. by s. 2, ibid., (w.e.f. 14-10-2009).`
